  "footnotes": [
    "Eastern Yan (Gongsun regime): Warlord state controlling Liaodong, 189–238 CE; conquered by Cao Wei.",
    "Eastern Xia (Dongxia / 大真): Jurchen splinter state in eastern Manchuria under Puxian Wannu, 1215–1233.",
    "Five Nations Dept (Wuguofu / 五國部): Jin dynasty administrative unit managing far-north Jurchen clans along the lower Songhua and Amur rivers.",
    "Eastern Three Kings: Yuan dynasty Mongol appanage princes ruling eastern Manchuria under the Liaoyang Branch Secretariat.",
    "Gando/Jiandao: Disputed Sino-Korean border zone along the Tumen River; settled by 1909 Gando Convention ceding the area to China.",
    "Zeleny (Greens): Green Army partisan forces active in the Amur/Far East region during the Russian Civil War, 1918–1922.",
    "Hwanggumpyong: Small North Korean island at the mouth of the Yalu River, subject of a 2011 joint development agreement with China."
  ]
